AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Amt
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Fixed amount to be discounted from base price.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Created By
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Created By field indicates the user who created this record.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Client
AD_COLUMN.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Active
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_OBDISC_X
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Number of units that are required to be included in order to be possible to apply the discount. Once this number is reached, the discount can be applied, so it is possible to pay Y units instead of X.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Image
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A visual picture used to describe an item.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Defines a system image

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Gifqty
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
This field applies to "Buy X and get Y as Gift" discount type.
Using this field the gift units can be defined
In order to be possible to apply the promotion, it is required to include in the ticket all products defined in the list of products with the quantities defined by this field.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Price Adjustment
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The ability to raise or lower prices.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Promotion or Discount applied to a particular line (product) automatically by the system.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_OBDISC_Included Roles
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Role Selection Mode is the way Roles will be selected for discretionary discounts applied in POS.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Updated
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The date that this record was last updated
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Updated field indicates the date that this record was updated.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Role
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The profile of security for the user defining what windows and tabs they can see.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Role determines security and access a user who has this Role will have in the System.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Creation Date
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: The date that this record is completed.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Created field indicates the date that this record was created.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_OBDISC_Y
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Once "X Units" have been reached, Y represents how many of them need to be payed. For example being X 3 and Y 2, having 3 units, only 2 will be requested to be payed.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_OBDISC_C_Currency_ID
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Currency the price is defined in

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_OBDISC_Subtype
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Defines which lines are affected by the discount or promotion: *'''Cheapest''': All the discount is applied to the cheapest product. *'''Average''': Discount is distributed among all products calculating the average price of all of them and applying it based on the actual amount of each of them.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Approval_Required
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Discount requires approval from a supervisor to be applied
AD_COLUMN.HELP: When a discretionary discount that requires approval is applied in POS and the ticket is about to be closed, approval from a supervisor user/role will be requested before allowing to continue.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Is_Gift
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
This flag applies to "Buy X and get Y as Gift" discount type.
In order to be possible to apply the promotion, it is required to include in the ticket all products defined in the list of products. Those products set as gift will be completely discounted from the price.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Organization
AD_COLUMN.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_OBDISC_Distribute
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
This flag affects on how the discount is computed internally but doesn't have any effect in the Web POS UI.
When a discount is distributed, the discounted amount, even shown for a concrete line, is not only computed in this one but distributed between all the lines in the ticket.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Qty
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
This field applies to "Buy X and get Y as Gift" discount type.
In order to be possible to apply the promotion, it is required to include in the ticket all products defined in the list of products with the quantities defined by this field.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Upc
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A bar code with a number to identify a product.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Use this field to enter the bar code for the product in any of the bar code symbologies (Codabar, Code 25, Code 39, Code 93, Code 128, UPC (A), UPC (E), EAN-13, EAN-8, ITF, ITF-14, ISBN, ISSN, JAN-13, JAN-8, POSTNET and FIM, MSI/Plessey, and Pharmacode)

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Price
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Total price applied to the combination of all products participating in the Discount or Promotion.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Updated By
AD_COLUMN.HELP: The Updated By field indicates the user who updated this record.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obdisc_Percentage
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Percentage to be discounted from base price.
